olkhoz musicals of Ivan Pyr’ev and their urban counterpart, directed by Grigorii Aleksandrov. Like Stalin, Slavic moviegoers delectated tuneful melodies, mobile bodies in choreographed dance numbers, colorful costumes, and the notion that “all’s well that ends well.” Yet Slavic versions of the musical elaborated scenarios that differed from the Hollywood model. This volume examines the vagaries of this genre in both countries, from its early instantiations to its contemporary variations almost a century after its dramatic birth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aMusical filmszSlavic countriesxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  afilm musical, dance, song, bravura finale, parallel plotlines, reconciliation of polarities.1 aGoscilo, Helena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoscilo, Helena, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHolmgren, Beth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaganovsky, Lilya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOstrowska, Elżbieta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProkhorov, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProkhorov, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalys, Rimgaila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilmes, Justin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102354008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z97831113181